{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":12372,"name":"","username":"mike7e","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58956e/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-05T09:02:52.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHi,\u003cbr\u003e\nSo I am making a map editor for my game, I am using the following code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUnder HandleUpdate\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ccode\u003e\n\tif (input-\u0026gt;GetKeyPress(KEY_H)) {\n\t\tPaintBrush(Vector3::LEFT, 5);\n\t}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ethe function\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e[code]void CharacterDemo::PaintBrush(Vector3 center, int radius) {\u003cbr\u003e\nResourceCache* cache = GetSubsystem();\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003eColor pixel = cache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Image\u0026gt;(\"Textures/MAP.png\")-\u0026gt;GetPixel(1, 1);\nfloat lightness = pixel.Lightness();\nColor newColor = Color(217, 217, 217);\ncache-\u0026gt;GetResource\u0026lt;Image\u0026gt;(\"Textures/MAP.png\")-\u0026gt;SetPixel(1000, 1000, Color(500,0,0));\n\n\nTerrain* terrain = terrainNode-\u0026gt;GetComponent\u0026lt;Terrain\u0026gt;();\nterrain-\u0026gt;ApplyHeightMap();\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e}[/code]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eterrainNode is a public shared pointer\u003cbr\u003e\nbut whenever I press H I get the assertion failed error.\u003cbr\u003e\nDoes anyone know of a way to do this?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMany thanks!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:42.036Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":8,"readers_count":7,"score":46.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":2058,"topic_slug":"how-to-reload-terrain-heightmap-from-a-different-function","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":480,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12373,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-05T11:00:01.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eAre the terrain Node and Terrain Component created somewhere? Somewhere in your code you should have \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-i\"\u003eterrainNode = scene-\u0026gt;CreateChild(“Terrain”)\u003c/span\u003e as well as \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-i\"\u003eterrainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent()\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso does the log say anything about resources not found? Does you debugger tell you what causes the trouble?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: It might also be that you cannot set pixels that way.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:42.100Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2058,"topic_slug":"how-to-reload-terrain-heightmap-from-a-different-function","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12374,"name":"","username":"mike7e","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58956e/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-05T11:06:55.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003e[quote=“Modanung”]Are the terrain Node and Terrain Component created somewhere? Somewhere in your code you should have \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-i\"\u003eterrainNode = scene-\u0026gt;CreateChild(“Terrain”)\u003c/span\u003e as well as \u003cspan class=\"bbcode-i\"\u003eterrainNode-\u0026gt;CreateComponent()\u003c/span\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nAlso does the log say anything about resources not found? Does you debugger tell you what causes the trouble?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eEDIT: It might also be that you cannot set pixels that way.[/quote]\u003cbr\u003e\nThe terrain node and component are created in CreateScene(). However if I create the terrain every time I press H, then I can set the pixels that way. So setting the pixels definitely works\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:42.167Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2058,"topic_slug":"how-to-reload-terrain-heightmap-from-a-different-function","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":480,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12375,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2016-06-05T11:30:00.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"mike7e\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"title\"\u003e\n\u003cdiv class=\"quote-controls\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/m/58956e/40.png\" class=\"avatar\"\u003e mike7e:\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSo setting the pixels definitely works\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eRight, I think the other case was with a Texture2D not an Image. I am at a loss.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:12:42.227Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":7,"readers_count":6,"score":1.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2058,"topic_slug":"how-to-reload-terrain-heightmap-from-a-different-function","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":192,"hidden":false,"trust_level":0,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_suspended":true,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":12376,"name":"","username":"Lumak","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/l/8491ac/{size}.png","created_at":"2016-06-05T17:14:19.000Z","cooked":"\u003caside class=\"quote\"\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ecache-\u0026gt;GetResource(“Textures/MAP.png”)-\u0026gt;SetPixel(1000, 1000, Color(500,0,0));\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat looks suspicious. The pixel index of 1000 – is your texture size over 1000? Also,  the Color(500,0,0) eventually gets turned into UInt() and will correct that erroneous value of 500 but the rgb values should be from 0.0f to